*** SAYS-US *** – A PROPOSAL

This web site is a proposal to build web and mobile capability that will allow millions of people, world-wide, to voice their needs and take action to fulfill them!

We propose to enable people, as workers, consumers, retirees, students, unemployed, and prisoners, to safely

Read and write anonymous reviews, including complaints and praise, like jobvent did for jobs

About employers, landlords, vendors, governments, etc

To learn from each other – peer rating and advice, like reddit

To find each other – by relevant demographic

To find outside resources to help take action

Enabling individuals to anonymously voice their individual concerns, we propose this initiative for Social, Economic, Political, & Psychological Change

Against bullying, oppressive, destructive individuals and institutions
Institutions, born to solve problems, then cause new ones

We can recognize good practices and socially useful product and services
There are struggles everywhere around us

We can change institutions, companies, schools, and governments
Online tools, resources, and mechanisms can help - If we build them, people will use them

We will learn from one another as we go

Help us give Voice to the Voiceless — Power to the Powerless! 

Anonymous concerns can identify problems and unmet needs

Needed changes can be highlighted and requested

Dialogue, preferable, can fail due to an imbalance and intransigence of power

If so, other forms of action are available

Action can lead to solving problems

Solving problems can help individuals and change institutions

Small successes can lead to bigger efforts

Repeat

Allowing people a web and mobile facility to voice concerns has already been proven to work, even without “take action” links and tools!
Before it was eviscerated, jobvent.com collected 100,000 reviews, most critical, about almost 10,000 companies
says-us will help people to move from from anonymous concern to concerted action!